Fidus Writer Debian Packaging
==============================

This directory contains Debian packaging files for Fidus Writer.

For complete documentation on building and installing the Debian packages,
please see:

    docs/debian-packaging.md

Quick Start
-----------

Build packages:
    ./build-deb.sh

Install:
    sudo dpkg -i debian-build/fiduswriter_*.deb
    sudo apt-get install -f

Updating Python Version
-----------------------

To update to a new Python version (e.g., from 3.14.2 to 3.15.0):

1. Edit debian/rules:
   - Change PYTHON_VERSION=3.14.2 to PYTHON_VERSION=3.15.0
   - Change PYTHON_MAJORMINOR=3.14 to PYTHON_MAJORMINOR=3.15

2. Delete the build cache:
   rm -rf .python-build-cache

3. Rebuild:
   ./build-deb.sh

That's it! All references to python3.14 will automatically update to python3.15.

Files in this directory:
- control       Package metadata and dependencies
- rules         Build instructions (contains PYTHON_VERSION and PYTHON_MAJORMINOR)
- changelog     Version history
- copyright     License information
- *.service     Systemd service files (Python version auto-substituted)
- *.postinst    Post-installation scripts (auto-detects Python version)
- *.postrm      Post-removal scripts
- nginx-example.conf    Example nginx configuration
- README.Debian         User documentation (installed with package)

